{"bill":{"bill_id":1645398,"change_hash":"8cd7e5b105d0351619d62cff55180f95","session_id":1988,"session":{"session_id":1988,"state_id":46,"year_start":2023,"year_end":2023,"prefile":0,"sine_die":0,"prior":0,"special":0,"session_tag":"Regular Session","session_title":"2023 Regular Session","session_name":"2023 Regular Session"},"url":"https:\/\/legiscan.com\/VA\/bill\/SB994\/2023","state_link":"https:\/\/lis.virginia.gov\/cgi-bin\/legp604.exe?231+sum+SB994","completed":0,"status":2,"status_date":"2023-02-06","progress":[{"date":"2023-01-06","event":1},{"date":"2023-01-06","event":9},{"date":"2023-01-20","event":10},{"date":"2023-02-02","event":10},{"date":"2023-02-06","event":2},{"date":"2023-02-08","event":9},{"date":"2023-02-10","event":10},{"date":"2023-02-10","event":9}],"state":"VA","state_id":46,"bill_number":"SB994","bill_type":"B","bill_type_id":"1","body":"S","body_id":8,"current_body":"H","current_body_id":7,"title":"Corrections Ombudsman, Office of the Department of; created, report.","description":"Office of the Department of Corrections Ombudsman; created. Creates the Office of the Department of Corrections Ombudsman headed by an Ombudsman who is selected by a Corrections Oversight Committee, also created by the bill. The Committee is made up of four members of the General Assembly and 11 nonlegislative citizen members who monitor the activities of the Ombudsman and the Department of Corrections. The bill provides the Office's authority to conduct inspections at least once every three years and more often when warranted of Department or Board of Local and Regional Jails facilities and requires the Office to establish confidential telephone hotlines and online forms for concerns, complaints, and inquiries by inmates, their family members and advocates, and Department employees and contractors. In addition, the bill requires the Committee to conduct quarterly public hearings and submit an annual report to the Governor, the Attorney General, the Senate Committee on the Judiciary, the House Committee on Public Safety, and the Director of the Department. The provisions of the bill are contingent on funding in a general appropriation act. Office of the Department of Corrections Ombudsman; created. Creates the Office of the Department of Corrections Ombudsman headed by an Ombudsman who is selected by a Corrections Oversight Committee, also created by the bill. The Committee is made up of four members of the General Assembly and 11 nonlegislative citizen members who monitor the activities of the Ombudsman and the Department of Corrections. The bill provides the Office's authority to conduct inspections at least once every three years and more often when warranted of Department or Board of Local and Regional Jails facilities and requires the Office to establish confidential telephone hotlines and online forms for concerns, complaints, and inquiries by inmates, their family members and advocates, and Department employees and contractors. In addition, the bill requires the Committee to conduct quarterly public hearings and submit an annual report to the Governor, the Attorney General, the Senate Committee on the Judiciary, the House Committee on Public Safety, and the Director of the Department. The provisions of the bill are contingent on funding in a general appropriation act.","pending_committee_id":0,"committee":[],"referrals":[{"date":"2023-01-06","committee_id":168,"chamber":"S","chamber_id":8,"name":"Rehabilitation and Social Services"},{"date":"2023-01-20","committee_id":164,"chamber":"S","chamber_id":8,"name":"Finance and Appropriations"},{"date":"2023-02-08","committee_id":4177,"chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"name":"Public Safety"},{"date":"2023-02-08","committee_id":4576,"chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"name":"Public Safety: Subcommittee #2"},{"date":"2023-02-10","committee_id":147,"chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"name":"Appropriations"},{"date":"2023-02-10","committee_id":4194,"chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"name":"Appropria